definition.value: Subdivision of the viscerocranial mucosa located above the superior constrictor of the pharynx and extends upwards and backwards toward the occipital bone.
Subdivision of viscerocranial mucosa behind the opening of the pharyngotympanic tube. Examples: There are only two instances, right and left salpingopharyngeal folds.
Subdivision of viscerocranial mucosa in front of the opening pharyngotympanic tube. Examples: There are only two instances, right and left salpingopalatine folds.
Region of surface of viscerocranial mucosa which overlies the medial end of the pharyngotympanic tube. Examples: There are only two instances, right and left tori.

Region of surface of viscerocranial mucosa which overlies that part of the levator veli palatini that curves into the soft palate below the opening of the pharyngotympanic tube. Examples: There are only two instances, the right and the left.
